{
  "stem": "20089.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And since I wasn't a smoker, I either bought things that I wanted to send home on the black market, or I gave it to the people in the camps, the adults in the camps, who of course used it to buy themselves things on the black market.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a very lucrative market.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I would say that most-- most of the survivors were in-- on the black market.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In fact, my-- my uncle and my cousin in Munich, were very big shots in the black market, the godfathers of the black market.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the black market?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, except that I think I wasn't the only one.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We also got chocolates at PX and coffee.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think the three most-- the three biggest shortages on the-- on the German market was first cigarettes, then coffee, then chocolates.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if the displaced persons had any of those items, they could sell them on the black market to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they could get a lot of marks and even dollars.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because a lot of the Germans would trade things for dollars, and then buy from the displaced persons.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that it was after the Haganah period.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of the girls in the Jewish agency who worked with us-- I can't remember her name because she left very early in my period in-- in Rosenheim-- she had been in the Haganah.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A young girl, I would say she was about 21 at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she must have been about 19.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all the Palestinian Jewish agency people were idealists, who had only one-- one purpose.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was to get as many people across the borders into Palestine as possible.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I gave all my cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
